Feature share-audio — "分享录音" long-press menu item
======================================================

Java reference: src/feature_share_audio/AudioShareHelper.java

Key decision: the long-press "分享" button dispatches through
WiskySystemApiManager.openShareDialog(...) → com.wisky.se01's system share
activity (separate APK, we can't edit). The format row (Note/PDF/PNG/TXT)
is bitmask-negotiated with that system app; a privately-assigned new bit
would be ignored.

Raw Android ACTION_SEND + application/zip on this device only resolves to
Kindle / Bluetooth / GMS Nearby / OneNote / 1Password — *not* the OEM
email / local storage / cloud / third-party chat targets the user wants.

Workaround: bypass the format-picker half of Wisky's share dialog (keep
its share-target half). Zip the audio ourselves, then call the other
openShareDialog overload that accepts pre-built URIs:
    openShareDialog(int appType, ArrayList<Uri> fileUris)
which drives the same full-coverage share chooser.

---------------------------------------------------------------
NEW FILE: smali_classes2/com/wisky/modulenotemanager/ext/AudioShareHelper.smali

Static run(SidebarNoteFragment):
  · Iterates fragment.getMAdapter().getItems() → for each FileInfo with
    isChecked(), lists files in NoteFileUtil.INSTANCE.buildNoteAudioDir(id).
  · No audio → return silently.
  · Builds zip via blankj ZipUtils.zipFiles(Collection, File) into
    externalCacheDir ?: cacheDir.
  · Wraps zip File in a Uri via blankj UriUtils.file2Uri (which uses the
    pre-declared androidx FileProvider authority com.wisky.notewriter.provider
    already in the manifest).
  · ArrayList<Uri> → WiskySystemApiManager.Companion.openShareDialog(2, uris)
    → fragment.startActivity(intent).

